Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Place a #pot over medium-high heat with the @jasmine rice{150%g} and @water{300%ml} (double for 4p). Bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower heat to medium, cover with the #lid and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Remove the #pot from the heat and keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} (or until ready to serve).

Once ready, add @salt{1/4%tsp}, @sugar{1%tsp} (double both for 4p) and half the @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet}. Mix well to combine.

Meanwhile, trim and halve the @cucumber{2}(trimmed and halved lengthways). Scoop out the seeds. Chop widthways into small pieces.

In a #bowl, mix the remaining @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @sugar{1%tsp} (double both for 4p).

Add the cucumber and set aside to marinate, continuing to toss occasionally.

Mix the @aioli{1%sachet} with the @sweet chilli sauce{1%sachet}.

In a #bowl, mix the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @oil{2%tbsp} (double for 4p).

Toss the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%g} in the @mayo{2%sachet}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Next, toss the chicken in the breadcrumbs.

Place on a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle over a little oil.

Bake until golden and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> Notice a stronger smell from the chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @mushrooms{150%g}(roughly chopped).

Deseed the @chilli{1}(deseeded and finely chopped) and finely chop.

Place a large #pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Fry the mushrooms for ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir in the @ketjap manis{1%sachet}.

Place the @bao buns{1%pack} on a #plate (three at a time) and microwave covered for ~{1%minute}.

Keep covered until serving.

> Don't have a microwave? Place a pot with 2cm of water over high heat. Once boiling, place a colander lined with a baking sheet on the pot. Place the bao (3 at a time) on the baking sheet, cover and steam for 3-4 mins.

Fill the bao buns with the crumbed chicken and a little pickled cucumber.

Fluff up the rice with a fork and divide between #bowls{}.

Top the rice with fried mushrooms and the remaining pickled cucumber.

Drizzle the sweet chilli aioli over the bao buns.

Garnish with a scattering of chopped chilli (use less if you don't like spice).